messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I don't know. There's a lady lying out here on the sidewalk.
Okay. She's bleeding?
Yes, she's bleeding.
Are you with the lady now?
Yes, she's right here.
Okay, hold on one second here. Let me write down what you're saying, okay? Stay with me.
Okay.
How old is the lady?
I don't know. She's my neighbor. She just moved in like two days ago. She looks like she's probably in her early 30s.
Okay, and is she awake? Is she breathing?
Yeah, she's breathing. But she's going in and out.
Stay with me. What happened?
I don't know. I don't know.
Is she completely alert?
No, kind of. She's looking at me.
Okay, do you have an ambulance coming?
Yeah, we're going to get the ambulance started right now.
Hold on for me. Do not hang up, okay?
Okay, I won't hang up.
Where is she bleeding from?
I don't know. It's on her arms. Under her arm. I don't know exactly where it's coming from.
Okay, paramedics are on the way. Can you check if her baby is in there? She's got a four-and-a-half-year-old.
She just moved in.
So what exactly happened? Her husband shot everybody?
That's what she said. Her husband shot everybody.
Is the baby okay?
I don't know. Where did her husband go?
Do you know if he left or did he shoot himself?
I don't know. Did he leave or shoot himself?
Give me the address where the woman is, please.
4350 Heiden Way.
Okay, 4350. Hold on one second, you're doing a great job.
Okay.
Okay, and she looks like she's in her early 30s, right? Is she still responsive?
She's not really responsive, just kind of looking at me.
Okay. Just hang in there, everybody is coming. Is the bleeding under control?
I think so. I can't see an entrance wound.
Can you get a clean, dry cloth to press on the wound?
I’m getting something. Her hand looks like it's shot.
Press down firmly and don’t lift it up.
Okay, it doesn't look like she's bleeding out anymore.
Okay, where is her husband now?
I don't know, she's not answering.
Is there any way she can get herself outside the house?
She's already outside.
Okay, and how many people are in the house?
Three that I know of.
Are you in a safe spot?
Yes, I'm outside her house, but I don't want to go any closer.
Okay, that's good. The police are coming and they'll handle it. Just stay where you are.
Okay.
Can you see any movement in the house?
No, just music playing. I heard noise earlier.
Fire department is staged on Garrity. Just make sure you're safe.
I know, I'll try.
What's her husband's name? Is she able to tell you?
She's not talking.
Okay, just hang in there.
The ambulance and police are coming. They are almost there.
Okay. I hear sirens.
Alright. If you need to leave because you're in harm's way, do it. I don't want anybody else hurt.
Alright, I hear the sirens coming closer.
You're doing a wonderful job. Stay with me.
Okay.
Once they get there, follow their instructions, okay?
Okay, thank you.
